76561198128778995,Recommended,252530,30393182,Posted: 8 March,all,Rex__,"Great, enjoyable simulatorThe graphics may not be like ETS2 or ATS, even Fernbus. But this game is by far the most realistic bus simulator I've seen. When you 1st get the game and start, things can be tricky, the game is set by default to lock keyboard steering wheel (make the wheels lock when turning) so if your using a keyboard to drive you SHOULD turn this off. The mouse steering mode is much better though, it provides a more smoother and enjoyable experience.The game is tricky at the start, and you I would reccomend changing the controls the way you like them so it makes things easier. The tutorials are great, they are very detailed in telling you what to do, however, you can't change the keys or options during them.The graphics are not amazing but are fine for me, I don't mind about them anyway. There are some notable bugs and glitches and also graphic issues which are only solved by restarting the game. Some bugs include: slow buses, black textures, passengers stopping and will not board the bus and a major one is that sometimes no passengers appear at stops. Other than this, the game is fine. The game is set in 80-90's Berlin and is a highly realistic to what Spandau area looked backed then, bus stops and lines are real and so are the veichle repaints. The game is highly moddable, and you can change about anything from passenger numbers to making your own lines on the default map or any others on the map editor. I would suggest getting freeware maps from the internet as you will get bored after a while with the normal game. I have also purchased payware DLC via steam which are mostly maps and are great.Overall,  a great game for anyone who has an interest in it, highly reccomended."
